Layout Component vs Nested Routes
Layout Component	Nested Route
Shared UI	Parent-child route structure
Uses Outlet	Uses Outlet
Header/Navbar/Footer	Dashboard/Profile/Settings
Reusable page structure	Route organization

In practice, they are often used together.

Interview Questions
What is a Layout Component?

A reusable component containing shared UI such as header, footer, navbar, and an Outlet for page content.

Why use Layout Components?
Avoid code duplication
Centralize navigation
Improve maintainability
Create consistent UI
What is Outlet?

A placeholder where child routes are rendered.

<Outlet />
What is an Index Route?

The default route rendered when the parent route is accessed.

<Route index element={<Home />} />
